                  <handDesc>
                     <handNote xml:id="h1" script="Ethiopic">20th-century script;  careful hand.<note>
                           <p>Unknown</p>
                           
                        </note>
                        <note>
                           <p>The text and images are encompassed by black frame along the edges of the scroll.  </p>
                        </note>
                        <seg type="rubrication">
                           Executed in the main hand
                           
                        </seg>
                     </handNote>
                  </handDesc>
                  <decoDesc>

                     <decoNote type="other" xml:id="d2"/>
                     <decoNote type="mixed" xml:id="d3">
                        <p>Three crude polychrome (red, brown, white, black) pictures:</p>
                        <p>
                           <locus target="#1"/>) An angel with a sword and scabbard (at the top of the scroll)</p>
                        <p>
                           <locus target="#2"/>) A face framed with eight “horns” and four squares, after Text II, also called “The Net of Solomon” (see Wagner <locus target="#1967"/>:<locus target="#725"/>or “The Seal of Solomon”, see Burtea <locus target="#2007"/>)</p>
                        <p>
                           <locus target="#3"/>) Four squares and a cross in the middle, in the midst of Text III</p>
                        <p>
                           <locus target="#4"/>) A face framed with eight “horns” and four squares (“The Net of Solomon”), at the bottom of the scroll.</p>
                        
                     </decoNote>
                  </decoDesc>
                  <additions>
                     <list>
                        <item xml:id="a1">
                           <p>በስመ፡አብ፡"... ወንጌል፡ ዘዮሐንስ፡ ቀዳሚሁ፡ ቃል፡ ወእግዚአብሔር፡ ውእቱ፡ ቃል፡ወቦቱ፡ ኵሉ፡ ኮነ፡ ወዘእንብሌሁ፡ አልቦ፡ ዘኮነ፡ በእንቲአሁ፡ ቦቱ፡ ሕይወት፡…</p>
                           
                        </item>
                     </list>
                  </additions>
                  <bindingDesc>
                     <binding contemporary="true">
                        <decoNote xml:id="b1">
                           <p>Scroll made of three pieces of thin, finely processed parchment (ca. <locus target="#77 #74"/>and <locus target="#42"/>cm long) sewn together with narrow leather strips. A leather fastening strap is inserted into the upper edge of the scroll.</p>
                           
                        </decoNote>
                     </binding>
                  </bindingDesc>
